Tables

Note that the pnwflights14 package includes several other data sets that may be of use and/or interest: mappings from two-letter airline codes to airline names, weather conditions, etc.

data("flights", package = "pnwflights14")
data("weather", package = "pnwflights14")
data("airports", package = "pnwflights14")
data("airlines", package = "pnwflights14")

Question 1

Which airlines had the best and worst track records of on-time departures in each month? Is it different between PDX and SEA?

worst_flight <- flights %>%
  select(month, carrier, origin, dep_delay) %>%
  group_by(month, carrier, origin)%>%
  arrange(desc(dep_delay))%>%
  group_by(month)%>%
  slice(1)%>%
  ungroup()
worst_flight %>%
  gt() %>%
  tab_header(title = "The worst track records of on-time departures", subtitle = "(Delay in minutes)")%>%
  cols_label(month = "Month", carrier = "Carrier", origin="Origin", dep_delay = "departure delay") %>%
  cols_align(align = "center", columns = c(month)) %>%
  tab_style(cell_text(align = "right"),locations = cells_title(groups = c("subtitle"))) %>% 
  tab_style(cell_text(style = "italic"),locations = cells_title(groups=c("title")))

Question 2

What cities have the most service from Portland, and which have the worst? (which city received the most flights from Portland, which received the least?)

number_flights_desc <- flights %>%
     filter(origin=='PDX') %>%
     count(dest)%>%
     arrange(desc(n))%>%
     slice(1:10)

number_flights_desc %>% 
  gt()%>%
  tab_header(title="The number of flight from PDX to different cities") %>%

  cols_align(align="center", columns=c(n)) %>%

Question 3

Which specific aircraft (tailnum) are seen most often, for whom do they fly, and on what routes?

aircraft_info <- flights %>%
    mutate(route=paste(tailnum, ': ' ,origin,'-', dest,sep = ''))%>%
     count(route)%>%
     arrange(desc(n))%>%
     slice(1:10)
aircraft_info %>% 
  gt()%>%
  tab_header(title="Flights of aircrafts") %>%
  cols_label(route="Aircraft", n="Number of lights") %>%

Which specific aircraft accumulate the most flight time?

flight_time <- flights %>%
  group_by(tailnum)%>%
  summarise(time_sum=sum(air_time,na.rm = TRUE))%>%
  arrange(desc(time_sum))%>%
  slice(1:10)

flight_time %>%
  gt()%>%
  tab_header(title="Accumulate flight time of aircrafts", subtitle="(Time in minutes)")%>%
  cols_label(tailnum="Aircraft", time_sum="Flight time") %>%
  cols_align(align="center", columns=c(time_sum))%>%
  tab_style(cell_text(align = "right"),locations = cells_title(groups = c("subtitle"))) %>% 
  tab_style(cell_text(style = "italic"),locations = cells_title(groups=c("title")))

Which specific aircraft log the most distance?

distance_aircraft <- flights %>%
  group_by(tailnum)%>%
  summarise(distance_sum=sum(distance,na.rm = TRUE))%>%
  arrange(desc(distance_sum))%>%
  slice(1:10)
distance_aircraft %>% 
  gt()%>%

Analysis of Face Availability

bold_n <- f %>% 
  select(FamilyName, Bold)%>%
  distinct(FamilyName,Bold)%>%
  count(Bold=="TRUE")

bold_pro <- bold_n$n[2]/bold_n$n[1]
Italic_n <- f %>% 
  select(FamilyName, Italic)%>%
  distinct(FamilyName,Italic)%>%
  count(Italic=="TRUE")

Italic_pro <- Italic_n$n[2]/Italic_n$n[1]

Number of Fonts per Family

number_fonts <- fonttable()%>%
  group_by(FamilyName)%>%
  count()%>%
  ungroup()
number_fonts_gt <- number_fonts %>%
  gt()%>%
  tab_header(title="Number of fonts per family")|>
  cols_label(FamilyName="FamilyName", n="Number of font") |>
  cols_align(align="center", columns=c(n))|>
  tab_style(cell_text(style = "italic"),locations = cells_title(groups=c("title")))

Display

d = flights |>
  filter(carrier %in% c('AA','AS','UA','US'))|>
  select(month, carrier, dep_delay) |>
  group_by(month,carrier)|>
  summarise(mean_dep_delay=mean(dep_delay,na.rm=TRUE))|>
  ungroup()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'month'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
ggplot(d)+
  geom_line(aes(x=month,y=mean_dep_delay,group=carrier,color=carrier))+
  labs(title = "Average departure delay time of four carriers",
       subtitle = "(in minutes)",
       x = "Month",
       y = "Average departure delay time")+
  theme(plot.title    = element_text(family = "Noto Serif"),
        plot.subtitle = element_text(family = "Noto Serif"),
        axis.text.x   = element_text(family = "Noto Sans"),
        axis.text.y   = element_text(family = "Noto Sans"))
